# Project documentation for Cursor

Canonical documentation for this codebase is under **`docs/`** (workspace-relative). It is part of the repo and should stay readable to the AI—do not move it outside the workspace or add ignore rules that exclude it without replacing this guidance.

When planning or implementing non-trivial changes, read the relevant files:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docs/README.md` | Setup, scripts, architecture overview |
| `docs/AGENTS.md` | Agent notes and Next.js guidance |
| `docs/CLAUDE.md` | Pointers to agent docs |
| `docs/DECISIONS.md` | Architectural decisions |
| `docs/CONTRIBUTING.md` | Contribution workflow |
| `docs/implementation-plan.md` | Planned work |
| `docs/folder-structure.md` | Layout conventions |
| `docs/requirements-analysis.md` | Requirements analysis |
| `docs/requirements-gap-analysis.md` | Gaps vs requirements |
| `docs/frontend-assignment.txt` | Assignment brief |

Use normal file reads when you need detail; prefer these sources over guessing project conventions.
